==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hectocotylus
<hw>Hec`to*cot"y*lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Hectocotyli</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ a hundred + <?/ a hollow vessel.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of the arms of the male of most kinds of cephalopods, which is
specially modified in various ways to effect the fertilization of the
eggs. In a special sense, the greatly modified arm of Argonauta and
allied genera, which, after receiving the spermatophores, becomes
detached from the male, and attaches itself to the female for
reproductive purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hectogram</ent>⟦br⟧
